snippet.textDisplay: back in about 2000 bought a 1992 Plymouth Caravan V6 with ~200,000 miles on it (320,000km).   Why ?  because it was in extraordinarily good condition, used only for commuting on the highway.   What it cost?  USD$800.00 plus about $125 for a fuel pump.   drove it for years and years giving it some replacement parts from time to time.  Sold it to a neighbor after he backed his truck up into it for about $500.  {and so it cost $300 plus parts over the years} ...Then bought a 2002 Chrysler T&C minivan, had about 100,000 miles (160,000km) drove it for about 10 years until about 185,000 miles (300,000 km) when the trans blew.   That Van was quite deluxe and when new was USD$32K new, I got for ~6K and sold for  $300 to the transmission shop.  So it cost me a brutal $600/year plus minimal parts.
